    "name": "The First Steps",
    "profile": "Late 70s, New wave , Mod influenced band from Worlington, Suffolk, UK made of two sets of brothers, Chris and Jem Murrell ( bass and drums ) and Jonny and Phil Thornalley ( manager and guitarist ).\r\n\r\nThey released two late 70's singles on their own label, English Rose Records. \r\n\r\nOn its release 'The Beat is Back' gained enthusiastic support and airplay from BBC Radio One DJs Mike Read and John Peel. This alerted a major label , A&M, but the meeting with A&R exposed the lack of ambition within the band. \r\n\r\nThe second single the sarcastic, 'Anywhere Else But Here', fared less well and the band folded.\r\n\r\nOnly 1000 copes of each 7\" vinyl single were manufactured. \r\n\r\nBoth singles have three tracks. All songs written by Chris 'Chip' Murrell and Phil Thornalley with vocals by Chip and Phil. Occasional drums by Will Gosling. \r\n\r\nChris and Phil went on to write songs recorded by 80s pop band Johnny Hates Jazz. ( The 'Johnny' was in fact Jonny Thornalley . A name coined at a house party and",
